## purpose
Defines policy constraints for nation.

## policy_rules
Nation policy constrains:
- who belongs within a national scope
- what authority is valid inside that scope
- what nation detail may be disclosed
- when cross-nation actions are valid
- when national paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- jurisdiction scope must be explicit
- belonging scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- cross-nation allowance must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public nation summary
- bounded nation detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical nation detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow nation-bounded action only for valid jurisdictional scope
- allow cross-nation path only for explicit allowance
- allow historical nation reference only in valid mode
- deny hidden jurisdiction widening
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If nation identity,
jurisdiction,
belonging,
cross-nation scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- jurisdiction policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- cross-nation policy is explicit
- denial behavior is explicit
